<document xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/XDOC/2.0"
  xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
  xsi:schemaLocation="http://maven.apache.org/XDOC/2.0 http://maven.apache.org/xsd/xdoc-2.0.xsd">
    <properties>
        <title>Install guide</title>
    </properties>
    <body>
        <section name="Install guide">
            <p>
                If some of the steps are unclear you can find more documentation on plugins at
                <a href="http://www.onehippo.org/cms7/documentation/development/plugin-development/user+interface/hello+world+plugin.html">
                    the plugin tutorial</a>.
            </p>
        </section>
        <section name="Obtaining the plugin">
            <p>
              Each release of the plugin is deployed into a Maven repository.
            </p>
        </section>
        <section name="Compile the jar into your war archive">
            <p>
                Add this dependency to the pom.xml of your CMS module.
                Look for the dependencies section and add the following code:
            </p>
<source><![CDATA[<!-- Hippo CMS Tagging plugin -->
<dependency>
  <groupId>org.onehippo.forge</groupId>
  <artifactId>ecm-tagging</artifactId>
</dependency> ]]></source>
          <p><span class="note">Note:</span> on <strong>Hippo 7.8</strong> and later, be sure to use startup option <code>-Drepo.bootstrap=true</code>
            for initializing the types, see
            <a href="http://www.onehippo.org/7_8/library/concepts/content-repository/content-bootstrap.html">Content Bootstrap</a></p>
        </section>

    </body>
</document>
